+## D-165 — Remove category defaultValue so intake wizard asks category
+**Date:** 2026-04-11
+**Commit:** `948c839`
+
+**Symptom (verified):**
+After D-163 reordered the wizard to commerce-first
+(category → productType → price → sizes → stock → ...), operators
+reported that productType and price were being asked but the category
+step was silently skipped on fresh Telegram products. The operator
+never got to pick from the CATEGORY_OPTIONS keyboard.
+
+**Root cause (verified):**
+`src/collections/Products.ts` line 448 declared
+`defaultValue: 'Günlük'` on the `category` select field. Payload applies
+`defaultValue` at create time whenever the incoming data does not include
+the field. The Telegram intake path in `src/app/api/telegram/route.ts`
+at `payload.create({...})` line 2388 only sets category when either the
+caption parser or Claude Vision returned one
+(`...(category ? { category } : {})`). When neither did, Payload filled
+in `'Günlük'` and the product was born already-categorized.
+
+The wizard step selector in `src/lib/confirmationWizard.ts` line 407
+checks `if (!product.category && !collected.category) return 'category'`.
+`product.category === 'Günlük'` is truthy, so the check failed and the
+category step was skipped — exactly the "default placeholder counting
+as a confirmed business choice" pattern the operator flagged.
+
+**Why this was the right fix (not a wizard-logic patch):**
+The wizard's step selector is correct — it uses `!field` as the
+"missing" signal, which is how every other step works. Patching the
+wizard to treat `'Günlük'` as "maybe-default, maybe-real" would be
+fragile (what if 'Günlük' is the operator's real choice?). The cleanest
+invariant is: **a field that was never explicitly set by an operator
+should read as null, not as a Payload-injected default.** Removing the
+defaultValue enforces that invariant at the data layer.
+
+**Fix applied:**
+Removed the `defaultValue: 'Günlük'` line from the category field
+definition in `src/collections/Products.ts`. Added an inline comment
+noting the D-165 rationale and confirming all reader sites are
+null-safe.
+
+**Files changed:**
+- `src/collections/Products.ts` — removed defaultValue + rationale comment
+
+**Blast radius (verified null-safe at every read site):**
+- `contentPack.ts` — `category: product.category ?? null`
+- `shopierSync.ts` — `localCategory` null-safe, falls back to first
+  available Shopier category with a warning log
+- `(app)/page.tsx` — `CATEGORY_LABELS[p.category] || p.category || 'Günlük'`
+- `geobotRuntime.ts` — `if (product.category) lines.push(...)` guarded
+- `imagePromptBuilder.ts` — `categoryLabel(category?: string | null)`
+
+Existing database rows are unaffected. This is a go-forward behavior
+change — any product already stored with `category: 'Günlük'` (real or
+default) keeps its value. For in-flight products mid-wizard that were
+born before D-165, operators can re-pick category via admin if needed.
+
+**Result:**
