+## D-166 — Make wizard session persistence awaitable (fix silent drop)
+**Date:** 2026-04-11
+**Commit:** `81a533b`
+
+**Symptom (verified via operator screenshot):**
+Bot sent the "💰 Fiyat girin (₺): / Örnek: 899 veya 1299.90" prompt.
+Operator replied "899". Bot sent NO reply — not the success ack, not
+the parse-error warning, not the catch-block "Sihirbaz hatası". Pure
+silent drop. The wizard sat frozen mid-step.
+
+**Root cause (verified):**
+`src/lib/confirmationWizard.ts` declared `persistWizardSessionBackground`
+and `deleteWizardSessionBackground` as fire-and-forget: they called
+`pool.query(...)` with a `.catch(warn)` tail but no `await`, and
+`setWizardSession` / `clearWizardSession` were synchronous `void`
+functions that invoked them without awaiting.
+
+On Vercel serverless, once the `/confirm` handler returned its
+`NextResponse.json({ ok: true })`, Vercel froze the Lambda. The
+in-flight `wizard_sessions` DB write could be cut off before it
+drained. The operator's follow-up "899" text message then landed on
+a cold Lambda (or a different warm instance), called
+`hydrateWizardSession(payload, chatId, msgUserId)`, found no row in
+`wizard_sessions` (previous write never completed), returned null,
+and the wizard text interceptor's `if (wizSession) { ... }` block was
+skipped entirely. The request fell through to photo handler (no match)
+and command handlers (no match) and returned 200 silently. Every
+wizard state transition (30+ `setWizardSession` callsites) had the
+same race; the `/confirm` creation path was just the most visible.
+
+**Fix (3 parts):**
+
+1. **Awaitable persistence** in `src/lib/confirmationWizard.ts`:
+   - Renamed `persistWizardSessionBackground` → `persistWizardSession`,
+     changed to `async function ... Promise<void>`. Internal try/catch
+     preserved so Neon transient failures still do not 500 the webhook.
+   - Same rename + async conversion for `deleteWizardSession`.
+   - `setWizardSession` signature now
+     `async (chatId, state, userId?): Promise<void>`, internally
+     awaits persistWizardSession.
+   - `clearWizardSession` same pattern.
+   - `getWizardSession`'s stale-session cleanup path still uses
+     fire-and-forget `void deleteWizardSession(...)` because
+     `getWizardSession` is sync by design and a missed stale delete
+     self-cleans on the next hydrate (which filters
+     `started_at > NOW() - INTERVAL '30 minutes'`).
+
+2. **36 await insertions** in `src/app/api/telegram/route.ts`:
+   Every callsite of `setWizardSession(...)` and `clearWizardSession(...)`
+   now has `await`. Covers /confirm startup, /confirm_cancel,
+   callback_query handlers for wz_cat/wz_ptype/wz_size/wz_target/
+   wz_confirm, and all per-step text interceptor handlers. All
+   callsites were already inside the main async POST handler so no
+   signature changes were required.
+
+3. **Defensive null-wizSession fallback** in the text interceptor
+   at `src/app/api/telegram/route.ts` line ~2189. When
+   `hydrateWizardSession` returns null but the incoming text matches
+   a wizard-input heuristic (`^\d+([.,]\d+)?$` for price,
+   `^\d{2}([,\s]+\d{2})+$` for size list, or `^\d{2}-\d{2}$` for
+   size range), the bot now sends "ℹ️ Aktif sihirbaz oturumu
+   bulunamadı — /confirm <ürün_id> ile yeniden başlatabilirsiniz"
+   instead of the previous silent drop. This is a safety net for
+   session expiry (30 min timeout), Neon transient outages, and any
+   future race not yet diagnosed.
+
+**Files changed:**
+- `src/lib/confirmationWizard.ts` — persist/delete made async and
+  awaitable; setWizardSession/clearWizardSession made async
+- `src/app/api/telegram/route.ts` — 36 `await` insertions + defensive
+  null-wizSession else branch in text interceptor
+
+**Latency impact:**
+Each `setWizardSession` now waits for a Neon INSERT/UPDATE
+(~20–60ms on warm pool). Typical Telegram webhook has 1–3
+setWizardSession calls, so added latency is ~60–180ms per request.
+Acceptable for an operator-in-the-loop flow.
+
+**Typecheck:** 3 pre-existing baseline errors (next.config.ts,
+(app)/page.tsx, collections/Products.ts:304 storyTargets) — identical
+before and after, verified via git stash.
+
+**Verification plan:**
+1. Start a fresh `/confirm <id>` in Telegram.
+2. Let the wizard advance to the price step.
+3. Reply with a plain number ("899").
+4. Expect: `✅ Fiyat: ₺899` followed by the next prompt.
+5. Repeat across several fresh products to confirm the race is gone.
+6. Additional: start a wizard, wait >30 min, then reply with a
+   number — expect the new "ℹ️ Aktif sihirbaz oturumu bulunamadı"
+   fallback message instead of a silent drop.
 
-**Status:**  
-ACTIVE — Architecture defined, implementation phases planned
+**Status:** ACTIVE
 
 
