+## D-167 — Mirror-extend padding — permanent frame elimination
+**Date:** 2026-04-12
+**Commit:** `cef930a`
 
-2. **Highlights** (commercePack.highlights):
-   - Rendered as a checkmark list under "Ürün Özellikleri" heading
-   - Only shows if array has valid string entries
-   - Gracefully hidden if empty
+**Symptom (verified via operator screenshot):**
+Brown suede sneaker on gray concrete floor. All 3 generated slots
+had visible rectangular frames — a clear boundary between the shoe
+photo area and the surrounding generated scene.
 
-3. **FAQ** (discoveryPack.faq):
-   - New `ProductFAQ` client component with expand/collapse accordion
-   - Renders below the product info grid
-   - Only shows if FAQ array has valid {q, a} entries
-   - Gracefully hidden if empty
+**Root cause (verified — 5th incident in the same chain):**
+Every previous padding approach used a SOLID COLOR:
+  - v50 (D-129/D-164): paddingRGB = bgRGB (scene target)
+  - D-157: paddingRGB = edge-sampled reference color
+  - D-161: paddingRGB = white fallback
 
-4. **SEO Meta** (discoveryPack → fallback):
-   - `generateMetadata()` export for Next.js head management
-   - Title: `discoveryPack.metaTitle` → fallback "{title} — UygunAyakkabı"
-   - Description: `discoveryPack.metaDescription` → `websiteDescription[:160]` → `description[:160]`
-   - Keywords: from `discoveryPack.keywordEntities` if present
-   - OpenGraph title + description set
+ALL of these create a visible rectangular boundary whenever the
+reference image's own background differs from the padding color.
+For this shoe: reference background = gray concrete; scene target
+= warm cream (#F5F1E6). The cream padding ring around the gray
+photo creates a hard edge Gemini preserves as a frame in its output.
 
-5. **JSON-LD Product** structured data:
-   - Schema.org Product with name, description, sku, brand, color, material, price, availability, image
-   - Uses websiteDescription (Geobot → fallback) for description
-   - Injected via `<script type="application/ld+json">`
+**No solid color can fix this.** The problem is structural.
 
-6. **JSON-LD FAQPage** structured data:
-   - Only emitted when FAQ exists
-   - Schema.org FAQPage with Question + Answer entities
-   - Injected via separate `<script type="application/ld+json">`
+**Fix (permanent):**
+Replaced all solid-color padding with Sharp's `extendWith: 'mirror'`.
+The reference image's edge pixels are mirrored outward, creating a
+seamless continuation of whatever background the photo already has.
+Zero color boundaries. Nothing frame-shaped for Gemini to copy.
 
-7. **Bonus: originalPrice + color + material** rendering added to product info grid
+Implementation (both `generateByEditing` and `generateByGeminiPro`):
+  1. `sharp(ref).resize(fitW, fitH)` — scale to fit inside 768x768
+     without adding letterbox bars
+  2. `.extend({ ..., extendWith: 'mirror' })` — pad to 768x768 with
+     mirrored edges
+  3. `.extend({ top:128, bottom:128, left:128, right:128,
+     extendWith: 'mirror' })` — pad to 1024x1024
 
-**Files Changed:**
-- `src/app/(app)/products/[slug]/page.tsx` — Full rewrite with content wiring
-- `src/components/ProductFAQ.tsx` — New client component for FAQ accordion
+`paddingRGB` (bgRGB) retained as variable for logging only. Not used
+in any Sharp operation.
 
-**Fallback Safety:**
-Every content field has graceful fallback: Geobot content → basic field → hidden. The page works identically to before if no Geobot content exists.
-
-**Status:**  
-ACTIVE — Phase A complete
+Sharp version 0.34.5 (requirement: >= 0.32.0 for extendWith support).
 
+**LOCK_REMINDER_BLOCK status:**
+Rule 1 (NO FRAMES) and Rule 2 (BACKGROUND MATCH) remain as prompt
+text guards. Mirror-extend ensures the INPUT IMAGE itself no longer
+violates them before Gemini even starts processing.
 
----
+**Supersedes:**
+- D-164 "paddingRGB = bgRGB" locked rule — solid-color padding is
+  no longer used at all. The INTENT of D-164 (no visible inner
+  rectangle) is now achieved more correctly by mirror-extend.
+- D-157 / D-161 — both were attempts to match the padding to the
+  reference edge; mirror-extend makes this moot.
 
