+
+/**
+ * Measures the mean luminance of the product region (non-background pixels)
+ * and applies a deterministic gamma/linear correction if the image is too
+ * bright (washed out) or too dark (underexposed).
+ *
+ * Target band: mean luminance 100–170 for product pixels.
+ * Above 170 → darken (reduce gamma)  — fixes washed-out / high-key outputs.
+ * Below 100 → brighten (increase gamma) — fixes underexposed outputs.
